The paper proposes a new evolving and self-organizing controller for unmanned aerial vehicles, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms and control theory. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.SY is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of a stable closed-loop system using control theory. The other categories are also relevant as they involve the use of machine learning algorithms and robotics for the control of unmanned aerial vehicles.
